gov.ornl.csed.csiir.sava.stucco

Class EntityExtractor

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.ornl.csed.csiir.sava.stucco.EntityExtractor

  • public class EntityExtractor
extends java.lang.Object
    Identify and annotate domain-specific entities from unstructured text. 

     -- Example Usage --
 public static void main(String[] args) {
	  ObjectMapper mapper = new ObjectMapper();
	  try {
   	EntityExtractor entityExtractor;
		if (args.length != 2) {
			entityExtractor = new EntityExtractor();
		}
		else {
			entityExtractor = new EntityExtractor(args[0], args[1]);
		}
		String json = entityExtractor.getAnnotatedTextAsJson("Microsoft Windows XP. Apple Mac OS X.");
			
		//transform the JSON string into a Sentences instance
		Sentences sentences = mapper.readValue(json, Sentences.class);
	  } catch (Exception e) {
		e.printStackTrace();
	  }	
	}

        Parameters:

      • getLabels

        public Sentence getLabels(Sentence sentence)
        Label each word of a sentence with a domain-specific label. The sentence must be tokenized, tagged with parts of speech, and formatted with I-O-B tags before it can be given a domain-specific label.
        Parameters:
        sentence - the instance representing a sentence
        Returns:
        the Sentence instance with the addition of domain-specific labels

      • getAnnotatedText

        public Sentences getAnnotatedText(java.lang.String text)
        Execute the entire annotation process on the text. This process includes parsing into separate sentences, tokenizing each sentence into words, and annotating each word with a part of speech tag, I-O-B format tag, and domain-specific label.
        Parameters:
        text - the text to be annotated
        Returns:
        a Sentences instance that contains all the Sentence instances from the text

      • main
